{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/objc(pl)NSLocking","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/s16SendableMetatypeP"],"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"UnfairLock"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"UnfairLock is an appropriate lock for cases where simple and lightweight mutual exclusion is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"needed. It can be intrusively stored inline in a data structure without needing a separate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"allocation, reducing memory consumption and cost of indirection. For situations where something","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"more sophisticated like condition waits or FIFO ordering is needed, use appropriate higher level"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"APIs such as those from the pthread or dispatch subsystems."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The values stored in the lock should be considered opaque and implementation defined, they"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"contain thread ownership information that the system may use to attempt to resolve priority"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"inversions."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This lock must be unlocked from the same thread that locked it, attempts to unlock from a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"different thread will cause an assertion aborting the process."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This lock must not be accessed from multiple processes or threads via shared or multiply-mapped"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"memory, because the lock implementation relies on the address of the lock value and identity of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the owning process.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The name ‘unfair’ indicates that there is no attempt at enforcing acquisition fairness, e.g. an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unlocker can potentially immediately reacquire the lock before a woken up waiter gets an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"opportunity to attempt to acquire the lock. This is often advantageous for performance reasons,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but also makes starvation of waiters a possibility."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This lock is suitable as a drop-in replacement for the deprecated OSSpinLock, providing much"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"better behavior under contention."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/instruments\/unfairlock"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/init()"]},{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/lock()","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/try()","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/unlock()","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/withLock(_:)"],"anchor":"Instance-Methods"},{"generated":true,"title":"De